Class AnalyzeSweep

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.pj2.Task
      • AnalyzeSweep

  • public class AnalyzeSweep
extends Task
    Class AnalyzeSweep is a GPU accelerated parallel program that analyzes a cryptographic function by computing odds ratios. The program automatically sweeps through all possible combinations of the parameters.

    Usage: java pj2 AnalyzeSweep [-nt=NT] "function" A_file B_file "test" bitGroup_file [ A_start B_start BG_start NRR ]

    The function argument is a constructor expression for the Function object that implements the cryptographic function to be analyzed. (For further information about constructor expressions, see class edu.rit.util.Instance.)

    The A_file argument is the name of a file, each line of which consists of a constructor expression for the Generator object that generates a series of A input values for the cryptographic function.

    The B_file argument is the name of a file, each line of which consists of a constructor expression for the Generator object that generates a series of B input values for the cryptographic function.

    The test argument is a constructor expression for the Test object that computes a series of odds ratios from the outputs of the cryptographic function.

    The bitGroup_file argument is the name of a file, each line of which consists of a constructor expression for the BitGroup object that specifies a series of output bit groups to be tested.

    The AnalyzeSweep program analyzes the cryptographic function specified by the function argument, as follows:

    1. For each constructor expression in the A_file, create a Generator object and use it to generate a series of A inputs for the cryptographic function.

    2. For each constructor expression in the B_file, create a Generator object and use it to generate a series of B inputs for the cryptographic function.

    3. For each constructor expression in the bitGroup_file, create a BitGroup object.

    4. For each possible combination of an A input series, a B input series, and a bit group object, carry out an analysis of the cryptographic function using the Test object as described in the Analyze program, and report the number of nonrandom rounds detected. The maximum number of nonrandom rounds detected so far is also printed.

    If the optional -nt=NT flag is specified, NT gives the number of GPU threads per block. If not specified, NT = 768 is used.

    If the optional A_start, B_start, and BG_start arguments are specified, the program uses those as the starting indexes for the A input series, B input series, and bit group, respectively, and proceeds from there. This is intended for resuming an aborted analysis sweep in the middle. If these arguments are omitted, the analysis sweep starts at indexes 0, 0, 0.

    If the optional NRR argument is specified, the program uses that as the maximum number of nonrandom rounds found so far. This is intended for resuming an aborted analysis sweep in the middle. If this argument is omitted, NRR starts at 0.
